text: Hurlingham Partido is a partido of Buenos Aires Province, Argentina. It is in the Greater Buenos Aires urban area. The provincial subdivision has a population of about 176,505 inhabitants in an area of , and its capital city is Hurlingham, which is from Buenos Aires. Hurlingham is known for the Hurlingham Club, a sports and polo club named after the Hurlingham Club in Fulham, England. ==Districts== *Hurlingham, Buenos Aires *William C.
